          },
          "id": "call_yiMfSczWdk0yroFH5NN6ghGg",
          "type": "function"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "# Start Demo\nThe following is a brainstorm of what I'm thinking we should do for start.\nTotal time estimate: 7 - 8m.\n\nSome interesting cross-cutting concerns:\n- IQs (Web IQ, Fabric IQ, Foundry IQ, Work IQ)\n- A365 and agent observability\n\n## Sketch 1 - GitHub Copilot App is Awesome\nThis needs to be couched in an actual app story. \"We at [Company X] already had some existing software investments we wanted where we wanted to incorporate this agentic goodness. Since this is an active collection of projects, I thought I would show you how the GHC App can help.\"\n- tour through the copilot app\n- start with macro concerns\n  - home\n  - my work\n  - automations\n  - Quick chats\n- project concerns\n  - sessions and worktrees\n  - rubber duck\n  - canvas\n  - significant thing to work on (i.e. a skill to bring a copilot studio agent over)\n\n## Sketch 2 - Local Agents to Cloud\nMoving agents to the cloud\n\n*Part 1 - local agents*\n- Start in VSCode with some agent code\n  - one local running in windows that we want to promote to the cloud\n- start with local agent working on windows\n- try to do something bad - blocked because of MxC\n\n*Part 2 - Adding Microsoft and Foundry*\n- toolbox\n- IQ's - walk through all of the iq's available and tastefully add\n- Romance Elijah's demo\n\n*Part 3 - Microsoft Foundry - Custom Agent Factory*\n- deploy as hosted agent\n- agent works in its own vm in the cloud (maybe mxc crossover?)\n- traces / rubric generation / agent optimizer\n\n*Part 4 - Autopilot Agents*\n- Agents in Teams and M365\n\n## Sketch 3 - Hill Climbing\nWhat comes after agent optimization? Three levels of Fine Tuning:\n- Ground up with your own code + data\n- Ground up with you own data (and Foundry's help)\n- Ground up with M365 RLE\n\n## Sketch 5 - Security and Governance\nA taste as a bridge to \"Protect and Observe\"\n- A365 agentic management (overview, registry, map, requests)\n- Defender + MDASH (handoff)",
      "role": "tool",
      "tool_call_id": "call_AQjwLqA4sCiwMKWkzaqCxOi4"
    },
    {
      "content": "# Part 1A - Triage the Response in GitHub Copilot App\n\n## Row 0 [~20s]\n**Narrative:** - Competitor launches a new allergy treatment in November\n- Market position is at risk\n- Small cross-functional team forms to respond fast\n- Goal: assess impact and find where agents can help first\n**Actions:** - Open with the business trigger\n- Introduce the project manager and operations lead\n- Frame the goal: protect share by accelerating the next-gen product plan\n\n## Row 1 [~25s]\n**Narrative:** - Start in GitHub Copilot App\n- Use home, my work, automations, and quick chats as the team control surface\n- Move from broad status to the work that matters now\n**Actions:** - Tour home, my work, automations, and quick chats\n- Keep the pace brisk\n- Focus on active work, not a broad feature tour\n\n## Row 2 [~30s]\n**Narrative:** - Open the active launch project\n- Gather the facts, risks, and opportunity\n- Test whether the timeline can move across plants, materials, and equipment\n**Actions:** - Open the active supply chain or launch project\n- Show shared context and key work items\n- Highlight artifacts tied to the accelerated launch scenario\n\n## Row 3 [~30s]\n**Narrative:** - Use sessions and worktrees to keep threads of work clean\n- Use rubber duck and canvas to explore options\n- Turn discussion into a scoped path forward\n**Actions:** - Show sessions and worktrees\n- Briefly visit rubber duck and canvas\n- Position each tool inside the same team working loop\n\n## Row 4 [~35s]\n**Narrative:** - Land on the concrete next step\n- Bring the Production Planning agent or Copilot Studio artifact into the dev flow\n- Use that as the handoff into the next sketch\n**Actions:** - Land on the concrete next step\n- Show the Production Planning agent, skill, or Copilot Studio artifact\n- End on the handoff into code and agent development\n\n",
      "role": "tool",
      "tool_call_id": "call_MHQHI6JaUSMcP3yd5k1FYOZn"
    },
    {
      "content": "# Part 1B - Promote the Agent from Local to Cloud\n\n## Row 0 [~25s]\n**Narrative:** - Pick up the same Production Planning agent in code\n- Start in VS Code with the first version from the Operations BRD\n- Run it locally before promoting it\n**Actions:** - Open VS Code with the local Production Planning agent\n- Tie it back to the prior project context\n- Show that it already fits the supply chain scenario\n\n## Row 1 [~30s]\n**Narrative:** - Show the local agent doing useful work\n- Pull together plant, capacity, and materials context\n- Suggest run-order changes with risks visible\n**Actions:** - Run the local agent\n- Show outputs tied to capacity, materials, and equipment constraints\n- Highlight optimized run-order suggestions\n\n## Row 2 [~25s]\n**Narrative:** - Trigger a risky action\n- Show Windows and MxC containment\n- Make the security boundary visible\n**Actions:** - Attempt a bad or disallowed action\n- Show the containment or policy boundary\n- Make the Windows, Scout, or MxC guardrail visible\n\n## Row 3 [~35s]\n**Narrative:** - Add toolbox support and IQ grounding\n- Connect internal knowledge and external context\n- Show how the agent gets better business context\n**Actions:** - Introduce toolbox\n- Add the relevant IQs\n- Tie each addition to better business context for the agent\n\n## Row 4 [~35s]\n**Narrative:** - Move into Foundry\n- Choose the model and connect knowledge\n- Define the production deployment path\n**Actions:** - Open Foundry\n- Show model selection and knowledge connection\n- Define the hosted deployment path\n\n## Row 5 [~30s]\n**Narrative:** - Deploy as a hosted agent\n- Show traces, rubrics, and optimization hooks\n- Move from local testing to managed cloud execution\n**Actions:** - Show the hosted deployment result\n- Visit traces, rubrics, and optimizer views\n- Emphasize managed cloud execution\n\n## Row 6 [~30s]\n**Narrative:** - Surface the agent in Teams and M365\n- Keep approvals and human review in place\n- Show the agent in the flow of work\n**Actions:** - Surface the agent in Teams or M365\n- Show approval or sign-off steps\n- Emphasize the flow of work, not another product tour\n\n",
      "role": "tool",
      "tool_call_id": "call_7mdl2zk4MEmGA19g5ky2jVMP"
    },
    {
      "content": "# Part 1C - Improve the Agent\n\n## Row 0 [~20s]\n**Narrative:** - Start from live traces and outcomes\n- Ask how to make the agent better over time\n- Frame three practical improvement paths\n**Actions:** - Open on traces or quality views\n- Connect directly from the previous sketch\n- Set up the three improvement paths\n\n## Row 1 [~20s]\n**Narrative:** - Path 1: custom code plus custom data\n- Best when tight control matters\n- Shape both logic and grounding directly\n**Actions:** - Show the custom code plus custom data path\n- Point to the relevant code, data, or config artifacts\n- Position this as the high-control option\n\n## Row 2 [~20s]\n**Narrative:** - Path 2: your data with Foundry support\n- Use strong domain context already inside the business\n- Improve the agent faster with platform help\n**Actions:** - Show the Foundry-assisted path\n- Focus on enterprise data improving the agent\n- Keep the example tied to production planning\n\n## Row 3 [~20s]\n**Narrative:** - Path 3: M365 feedback and reinforcement loops\n- Learn from real usage, approvals, and outcomes\n- Improve behavior in the flow of work\n**Actions:** - Show the M365 feedback-driven path\n- Highlight approvals, feedback, or reinforcement signals\n- Keep the emphasis on real usage\n\n## Row 4 [~15s]\n**Narrative:** - Summarize the three paths\n- Reinforce that this is now a managed, improvable agent\n- Bridge to fleet visibility and governance\n**Actions:** - Summarize the three paths\n- Reinforce that the agent is now managed and improvable\n- Tee up the governance sketch\n\n",
      "role": "tool",
      "tool_call_id": "call_0ts0VUF0RjCyStLomkqYdu1x"
    },
    {
      "content": "# Part 1D - Govern the Agent and Hand Off to Protection\n\n## Row 0 [~20s]\n**Narrative:** - Shift from building agents to seeing and governing them\n- Open in Agent 365\n- Show the Production Planning agent as part of the broader fleet\n**Actions:** - Open Agent 365 or A365\n- Show the overview, registry, map, and requests\n- Make the Production Planning agent visible in the broader fleet\n\n## Row 1 [~20s]\n**Narrative:** - Make policy and posture visible\n- Highlight governance state and regulated-business context\n- Keep the healthcare angle as a proof point\n**Actions:** - Show posture, policy, and governance indicators\n- Highlight any regulated-business context that is visible\n- Keep the healthcare angle brief and concrete\n\n## Row 2 [~20s]\n**Narrative:** - Show security as part of the build and release loop\n- Scan code, validate risky behavior in a sandbox, return findings to developers\n- Fix issues before the agent ships\n**Actions:** - Show the security loop at a high level\n- Cover code scanning, sandbox validation, and returned findings\n- Tie the loop back to the developer workflow\n\n## Row 3 [~20s]\n**Narrative:** - Hand off to Defender and MDASH for deeper investigation\n- Bridge into the next part of the demo\n- Keep this section focused on build, promotion, and governance handoff\n**Actions:** - Open or reference Defender and MDASH\n- Use them as the handoff point\n- End on the bridge into Protect and Observe\n\n",
      "role": "tool",
      "tool_call_id": "call_yiMfSczWdk0yroFH5NN6ghGg"
    },
    {
      "content": null,
