    {
      "content": "# Start Demo\nThe following is a brainstorm of what I'm thinking we should do for start.\nTotal time estimate: 7 - 8m.\n\nSome interesting cross-cutting concerns:\n- IQs (Web IQ, Fabric IQ, Foundry IQ, Work IQ)\n- A365 and agent observability\n\n## Sketch 1 - GitHub Copilot App is Awesome\nThis needs to be couched in an actual app story. \"We at [Company X] already had some existing software investments we wanted where we wanted to incorporate this agentic goodness. Since this is an active collection of projects, I thought I would show you how the GHC App can help.\"\n- tour through the copilot app\n- start with macro concerns\n  - home\n  - my work\n  - automations\n  - Quick chats\n- project concerns\n  - sessions and worktrees\n  - rubber duck\n  - canvas\n  - significant thing to work on (i.e. a skill to bring a copilot studio agent over)\n\n## Sketch 2 - Local Agents to Cloud\nMoving agents to the cloud\n\n*Part 1 - local agents*\n- Start in VSCode with some agent code\n  - one local running in windows that we want to promote to the cloud\n- start with local agent working on windows\n- try to do something bad - blocked because of MxC\n\n*Part 2 - Adding Microsoft and Foundry*\n- toolbox\n- IQ's - walk through all of the iq's available and tastefully add\n- Romance Elijah's demo\n\n*Part 3 - Microsoft Foundry - Custom Agent Factory*\n- deploy as hosted agent\n- agent works in its own vm in the cloud (maybe mxc crossover?)\n- traces / rubric generation / agent optimizer\n\n*Part 4 - Autopilot Agents*\n- Agents in Teams and M365\n\n## Sketch 3 - Hill Climbing\nWhat comes after agent optimization? Three levels of Fine Tuning:\n- Ground up with your own code + data\n- Ground up with you own data (and Foundry's help)\n- Ground up with M365 RLE\n\n## Sketch 5 - Security and Governance\nA taste as a bridge to \"Protect and Observe\"\n- A365 agentic management (overview, registry, map, requests)\n- Defender + MDASH (handoff)",
      "role": "tool",
      "tool_call_id": "call_KGBUmf1cPF7gcQLL56pvTQUv"
    },
    {
      "content": "# Triage in GitHub Copilot App\n\n## Row 0 [~20s]\n**Narrative:** - Competitor launches a new allergy treatment in November\n- Market position is at risk\n- Small cross-functional team forms to respond fast\n- Goal: assess impact and find where agents can help first\n**Actions:** - Open with the business trigger\n- Introduce the project manager and operations lead\n- Frame the goal: protect share by accelerating the next-gen product plan\n\n## Row 1 [~25s]\n**Narrative:** - Start in GitHub Copilot App\n- Use home, my work, automations, and quick chats as the team control surface\n- Move from broad status to the work that matters now\n**Actions:** - Tour home, my work, automations, and quick chats\n- Keep the pace brisk\n- Focus on active work, not a broad feature tour\n\n## Row 2 [~30s]\n**Narrative:** - Open the active launch project\n- Gather the facts, risks, and opportunity\n- Test whether the timeline can move across plants, materials, and equipment\n**Actions:** - Open the active supply chain or launch project\n- Show shared context and key work items\n- Highlight artifacts tied to the accelerated launch scenario\n\n## Row 3 [~30s]\n**Narrative:** - Use sessions and worktrees to keep threads of work clean\n- Use rubber duck and canvas to explore options\n- Turn discussion into a scoped path forward\n**Actions:** - Show sessions and worktrees\n- Briefly visit rubber duck and canvas\n- Position each tool inside the same team working loop\n\n## Row 4 [~35s]\n**Narrative:** - Land on the concrete next step\n- Bring the Production Planning agent or Copilot Studio artifact into the dev flow\n- Use that as the handoff into the next sketch\n**Actions:** - Land on the concrete next step\n- Show the Production Planning agent, skill, or Copilot Studio artifact\n- End on the handoff into code and agent development\n\n",
